data.content:
## What breaks in .NET 11

**EF Core 11 fully removes sync I/O for the Cosmos DB provider.** In .NET 10 you could opt in to sync-over-async — that escape hatch is gone. All four of your repository methods will **throw at runtime**:

| Method | Broken call | Fix |
|--------|------------|-----|
| `GetAll()` | `ToList()` | `await ToListAsync()` |
| `GetById()` | `First()` | `await FirstAsync()` |
| `GetCount()` | `Count()` | `await CountAsync()` |
| `Save()` | `Add` + `SaveChanges()` | `SaveChangesAsync()` |

### Required fix

Convert the repository to async:

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
        => await _context.Products.ToListAsync();

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
        => await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
        => await _context.Products.CountAsync();

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

All callers must be updated to `await` these methods. There is **no opt-in or workaround** — the Cosmos provider now requires async throughout.
